---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const updated = new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
	year: "numeric",
	month: "long",
	day: "numeric",
});
const email = "hello@attentivebrain.com";
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy policy — attentivebrain"
	description="How attentivebrain handles your data: what we collect when you sign in or post a score, how it's used, and your choices. Plain language, no surprises."
	keywords="attentivebrain privacy policy, data, cookies"
>
	<main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-(--spacing-section)">
		<p class="text-caption text-ink-muted-48 mb-4 uppercase tracking-[0.04em]">Privacy policy</p>
		<h1 class="text-hero text-ink">Your privacy.</h1>
		<p class="text-caption text-ink-muted-48 mt-4">Last updated {updated}</p>

		<div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-ink-muted-80">
			<p>
				attentivebrain is built to respect your attention and your privacy. This policy
				explains, in plain language, what information we collect, why, and what control
				you have over it. We collect as little as possible.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Playing without an account</h2>
			<p>
				You can play attentivebrain without signing in or giving us any personal
				information. When you play anonymously, your scores stay on your device and are
				not sent to us. Your theme preference (light or dark) is stored in your browser's
				local storage so the site remembers it between visits — this never leaves your
				device.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">When you sign in</h2>
			<p>
				Signing in is optional and uses Google. If you choose to sign in, we receive
				basic profile information from Google — your name, email address, and profile
				photo — to identify your account and show your name on the leaderboard. You can
				edit the display name and photo we show at any time from your profile menu.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Leaderboard and scores</h2>
			<p>
				If you are signed in and finish a round, your best score (words recalled,
				attention span, and recall time) is stored so it can appear on the public world
				leaderboard alongside your chosen display name and photo. Only your best score is
				kept — not a history of every round. Score and profile data are stored with our
				infrastructure provider (Supabase) on your behalf.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">What we do not do</h2>
			<p>
				We do not sell your data. We do not use advertising trackers. We do not build
				behavioral profiles of you. We do not collect more than what is described above.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Your choices</h2>
			<p>
				You can stop sharing data at any time by logging out, after which anonymous play
				sends us nothing. To request deletion of your account data — your profile and
				leaderboard entry — email us and we will remove it. You can also clear the theme
				preference by clearing your browser's local storage.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Children</h2>
			<p>
				attentivebrain is intended for a general audience and is not directed at children
				under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Changes to this policy</h2>
			<p>
				We may update this policy as the product evolves. When we do, we will revise the
				"last updated" date above. Material changes will be reflected here.
			</p>

			<h2 class="text-display-lg text-ink pt-6">Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about your privacy? Email us at
				<a href={`mailto:${email}`} class="link-action">{email}</a>.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div class="mt-12">
			<a href="/" class="btn-primary">Back to the game</a>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>
